reviews.review_text: The vegetarian dumplings are DELICIOUS and very reasonably priced!  I love coming here for a cheap-ish meal of beer and dumplings, but I also love ordering the #7 for a special date night with beautifully-crafted cocktails.  The food Ive had with the #7 other than the dumplings was equally delicious.

BLND TGER is an incredible food experience. These hand made dumplings are on another level, with their taste and craftsmanship. Parking is great in the area if youre driving, with two parking lots in the area. The pricing for portion is fairly priced, really good value. No public washroom, so make sure you take care of business before coming down. Staff are friendly, and offer great suggestions. Highly recommend as a must stop in the area.

Love this hidden gem! Very warm and welcoming atmosphere. Perfect for any rainy nights in Vancouver. The cocktails menu is brilliant and creative, my favourite would be the Empire Jade. The food menu is also superb and seasonal. The Bison MoMos a must try and also by far the best Crispy Duck I ve had with the bread such such. The service was excellent.
No wait time (Sunday at 5pm). Drinks were good (little expensive. But it s downtown). Cool story for each drink. Bartender was very friendly. Very neat experience.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi Lisa, thank you for your kind words, you may be reviewing the wrong business as we are just a simple dumpling shop. We look forward to seeing you soon.

reviews.review_text: I m giving this place 5 stars based solely on the quality and innovation of the cocktails and the fantastic service. I really don t care for the eccentricity/secrecy, and the obviously-manipulated google reviews. I seriously don t believe that people waited several hours only to be turned away. If true, re-evaluate your plans. There are many options on this block.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi Paul, thank you for your kind words. We agree that East Georgia st has some amazing options that everyone should try. We look forward to seeing you soon.

reviews.review_text: Loved everything about this place except for the wait.. But what can you do when you live in a shoe.. Drinks & Dumplings were phenomenal! Excellent Service & Live Music!

I recently visited this speakeasy bar and had an amazing time! The atmosphere is cozy and intimate, with low lighting and comfortable seating. The drinks are expertly crafted, with a wide variety of options to choose from. Overall, I would highly recommend this speakeasy bar to anyone looking for a unique and memorable night out. Whether youre a cocktail connoisseur or just looking for a fun and relaxed atmosphere, this place has something for everyone.

We ordered several numbers; 3 (Pork), 4 (Bison) and 6 (Vegan). The last one was the most tasty. But give them a second to cool or youll burn your mouth. We ordered the No.7 too (One of the house specials) and it was VERY unique. This one will take a while to prepare so make sure to visit the Irish Heather opposite as you wait.
Slightly expensive dumplings but the lamb ones are truly amazing! Ask for the number 7 dumpling for access to the speakeasy (thank me later). Best speakeasy I have ever been to.

First thing they noticed us in our arrival was about the 1 hr wait list. Even though, we decided to wait and honestly it so worth the wait. We were in a group of 4 people, the experience was worthwhile, food is fresh, customer service is awesome. A friend suggested me their Pork belly, which might be their most popular because I never tasted anything similar. The architecture and environment are cozy. Really seems you are outside Vancouver for a little while.

What an amazing experience we had inside ;) Our server was such a delight and went above and beyond to accommodate my bridal party and I. I loved that each drink paired with a quirky story on their menu. Every exclusive cocktail had such a unique taste that showcased some interesting ingredients. Dont be shy to ask the bartender for their recommendation too! I appreciated they maintained the sanctity of a blind tiger by enforcing their own set of light rules. The decor and concept of LaoWai was very charming and I would easily revisit again.

Loved both options of the vegetarian dumplings while waiting for the #7! They were really tasty and I m usually quite picky with dumplings. The food inside is amazing too. All the staff are super friendly, welcoming, and very knowledgeable. Definitely a unique experience and I love this place every time.

Such a great place, the service was quick and friendly even on a busy night and a very comfortable atmosphere. An extensive drink menu to try out and all the dishes I tried were amazing. I believe it was the I heard a rumour cocktail was my favorite and the Pork Belly is a must have, highly recommend!

Had a great experience here last weekend, my girlfriend and I went on a date night and were completely blown out of the water by the level of care and hospitality by our server. The food was amazing and cocktails were all a hit. I would recommend this place to absolutely anyone looking to get away from their busy life and enjoy a night to unwind and enjoy quality time with their spouse, friends or family.

A hidden jade (gem) indeed! There is a long waitlist to get in (typically 2-3 hours +) so I would recommend putting your name down on the list and enjoying other food places nearby. -Bartenders: perfection. Extremely knowledgeable, friendly, and skilled. Our bartender put on a good performance with the other bartender when mixing drinks and they work harmoniously together. -Drinks: Each drink has a story and was very well thought out. We tried 4 drinks that night and we will be back to try more! Each drink was also very special and in my personal opinion the best bar Ive been to in Canada. *note* they do not allow usage of cameras in this place, but you can keep your phone in your jacket/purse.
So much fun! Smokin  cocktails, talented musicians, wonderful space and the wild boar dumplings are out of this world Dee-licious!

Whereislaowai is a Vancouver gem, it s so precious!! I ve been coming here for the last couple years and I m astonished by the service I get every time. The cocktails are out of this world. There s a story behind every sip from every cocktail you take. The food is chef s kiss, and the attention to detail with the decor makes this hands down my favourite speakeasy/cocktail lounge in Vancouver!!

Been here a couple times.  Really like the food and most of the drinks (some are too adventurous for me).  It s really cool layout inside and they have a no phone rule which really allows you to soak in the moment of being in a wonderful space.  Sometimes they have live music which is an added bonus.

Phenomenal atmosphere, cocktails and the best service we received in Vancouver. The booklet of cocktails is adorable and a very fun and clever way of presenting a drink menu. 10/10. I dont want to give away too much...just go and experience this wonderful place for yourself, you wont be disappointed.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi Courtney, it was a pleasure to host you. We look forward to seeing you again soon.

reviews.review_text: I came here last night for my birthday and ordered the number 7. From the moment we walked in, we were treated to one of the best customer service experiences Ive ever had. The staff were super attentive and its clear they really care about what they do. It was lovely to chat with them. The dumplings were delicious. The star was the crispy eggplant - we ordered two! We were told the cocktails are experimental and it shows - Ive never tasted flavours like this. Absolutely amazing. Ill definitely be coming back. No 1 star review from me   what a great small dumpling shop.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you for stopping by Sophie! We look forward to seeing you and your group again soon.

reviews.review_text: Waaww, this place is just amazing, from the decor to the well though out menu. Top points to everyone involved who has brought this place to what it is. Thanks Brett & Louis for the fabulous hospitality, I ll be back & I ll be sending many people your way too. Seeing these bad reviews about wait time annoys me, it s a brand new hidden gem which everyone wants to go to, so yes there is a wait and if you know it s 2 hours (which a lot of places are right now), either wait or run across the road to the Irish Heather for a couple before your spot opens up. Easy! Get down there people, you might have to wait but you won t be be disappointed!!
Dumplings here are great. I like the outdoor seating area. Lots of options for food and drinks in this neighborhood

Great speakeasy with a story book of amazing cocktails ! The bartender was engaging and made the experience that much better. Tasty dumplings and to top it all off some awesome live music. One of my favourite spots in Vancouver.

A hidden gem in Vancouver! If you haven t been here then you need to visit this place ASAP. Perfect spot for date night. Dumplings are delicious, fresh and excellent value. My girlfriend and I visited here last week and we left with a huge smile on our face. 5 star experience!

One of my favourite spots to visit whether its a night cap with friends or entertaining clients/out of towners. Creative cocktails, delicious small plates, and live music set in a beautiful room create the perfect environment for a good time. Love what theyre doing for Vancouvers bar scene.

Went to the speakeasy for the first time last night and I was blown away by the experience. You just need to know the password. ;) The dumplings I got were super tasty (lamb cumin and pork). We had two drinks each which were unlike any drink I ve ever had before. So unique. I really enjoyed the Mondrian (I think that s how it s spelled   it s the one with matcha and wasabi mist) and With Love From Russia (their take on espresso martini). Unreal! They also had jazz music playing 830 onwards  super cool atmosphere. Will definitely be back! Thank you for having us.

I will have to disagree with some of the reviews here!! There are definitely some wait times for a table but think about it, there is wait list because place is full .....and it is full for a reason!! Room is tastefully designed and decorated.  Cocktail list is very interesting and creative.  All the staff members are very knowledgeable and friendly.  We were pleasantly surprised by the food quality and flavor profiles. Overall 5* experience.  Its fun place to be in and very different compare to any other venue in Vancouver.  Its our new favorite place....will be back soon!!

First time ordering the number 7 and I had a great experience! Really nice ambience, delicious dumplings, and unique cocktails too. Definitely on the pricier side but our bartender, Ned, made it all worth it. Very entertaining throughout the night and had great recommendations based on our tastes. Can t wait to return!

I went with my fiance . A great date Night to say the least. I was skeptical of the food and drinks since I read negative reviews but our mixologist/bartend Ned was an absolute superstar. He was a great host and reason for us having a blast . We ordered everything on the menu to get a feel for the food ourselves and we were absolutely delighted with every dish . The servings were great for us two . As for the drinks. Amazing craft and showmanship with every order. Every item on the menu tasted unique and delicious. It definitely made our night , and we couldnt have been happier with the first time experience.

Excellent drinks and love the concept. The dumplings had a nostalgic taste to them as well. Overall, a very pleasant experience and would highly recommend visiting this location on an evening with live music.

First of all this little kiosk of a place that sells dumplings looked amazing!  WTF ?  Get outta here! It looked like an old fashioned Chinatown stalk from the 30 s but really cool and hipsterized.  Something my grandfather would have liked back in those days when he owned property accross the street which he sold for $2000.  A very long time ago.  I loved the concept.  A polite non Asian woman was tending the front of shop and I found out I could order frozen dumplings   for takeaway.  I can t remember the price but it wasn t cheap, but remember thinking they re handmade so should be good.  Asked which ones she liked which was option four, The Zhong (see picture of menu).  I asked if ok to take some photos and we got our little frozen gems which we used for our hotpot dinner at home.   TBH I was wondering if they would be a letdown but we were all surprised they held up well in the hotpot and you know what?  They tasted great.  Wasn t sure about the thick skin but that was the wrapping bonus because they were chewy and held up to the drenches of the rolling boiling hotpot soup and the tumbling abuses it got being stirred about and overcooked.  These were some hearty dumplings!  Best of all they were locally made and not some frozen factory made from overseas with sceptical ingredients.  I hope.   So A plus for these dumplings! But wait.  Nooooo way! It s a speakeasy? If you only knew the expletives that was shouting from my brain so early in the morning as I thumb this review on my smartphone. Now I have another reason to come here.  Ok sure one dude wrote he didn t have good customer service and another said the dumplings were chewy and the wrapper too thick.  To them I say Hah!!! Whatever.  I m just gonna enjoy the experience of it all.  Because regardless of that, I ve had and been through way way worse when I lived in Chinatown and this is a treat.  ( as long as I can afford it). If I were as young as these reviewers they d understand more of being appreciative for places like this that are revitalizing my childhood haunts.  Bringing back some mystery and life back into these buildings that have lived such amazing lives.  So the next time you come to Chinatown day or evening.  Dare to drop in here.  Experience something new that is so old with open eyes.  Don t be a stuffed up Millennial or Gen Z foodie know it all.  Just enjoy and live the experience and remember where we all came from.  Humble roots.

A truly unique experience, amazing signature drinks, delicious food, and amazing hosts, and bartenders. One word of caution, groups of two are seated in a small section, and the wait can be anywhere from 1-2 hours. That being said,  worth the wait. Will be coming back again next time in Vancouver.

Cant take photos in the back so come prepared to put your phone down for a few hours. Wonderful breadth of cocktails and dumplings. Will be back when Im in town again. Loved the atmosphere, creativity and expertise with the cocktail menu (it evolves frequently), and great waitressing!!

An amazing experience! I d heard great things about the drinks but the food was unexpectedly good! The smoky tofu noodles were excellent as was the lingcod and crispy eggplant! The cocktail menu was a hardcover with some of the most interesting drinks I ve ever had. Recommend the  Behind Blue Eyes  and  The Khan and I . Will definitely be back again soon!

It was a long wait but pretty worth. The ambiance is so nice and the Bartenders and Servers are so kind. Loved Jen. She was so kind and patient. She was amazing with helping us choose our drink and explaining the menu. The dumplings i did order the Zhong Dumpling were delish!!! I wish i ordered more!

This place SLAPS! The entrance through the freezer into the back Speakeasy had me audibly saying  wow . Dark, chic and cozy it felt like a different world. The cocktail menu was a lesson in story telling attaching each drink to historical figures from throughout Chinese history. Dinner and drinks with a friend, we ordered the whole gambit of dumplings. The variety in flavour was amazing. Struggled to pick my favourite because they were all so good. Would 10/10 recommend

Bring a smile and a sense of adventure, and the staff will lead you through an experience that dazzles the senses. We came here on a recommendation and a whim, and were blown away by the hospitality, flavors, and fun that was to be had. From cool shared fusion dishes, to cocktails with a story, finished with baiju you will never see around, our host and bartender Jen made our simple night out an adventure to remember. So journey back into the prohibition days and treat yourself and good company to an experience that is truly one of a kind (and make sure to ask for Jen!) P.s. no photos because its truly authentic!

The most fabulous meal & drink this 20+ country traveler has had maybe ever. Ethan is a phenomenal host. Our wait-person .. I think her name is Jen (sorry, assuming pronouns here) was. FULL STOP. incredible. She was so knowledgeable about every process to produce each ingredient and so helpful in navigating the Baijiu menu. Incredible experience.

We were so impressed with the thought and heart that went into crafting this restaurant, down to even the smallest detail. The owner & staff were incredibly friendly and thoughtful, giving us a truly unforgettable experience. Couldn t recommend this location more if you are looking for a unique night out in Vancouver!
Cocktails did not disappoint. Gorgeous decor (no photos allowed though). Best to try and get in with 3-5 people as limited 2 top tables.
We waited three hours for order 7 and it is super popular, but it took too long so we changed our order to 5. WE WILL BE BACK TO TRY ORDER 7! I am determined.

Service was fantastic - manager and bartender kept checking in on us and explaining the drink making process. We made a request and they were very accommodating. Got there just after 6 on a Friday and waited 30-40 min for seats for 2 at the bar, so be prepared for a bit of the wait on come earlier or later in the evening.

Wow what an experience! Chris absolutely killed it with the recommendations but I don t think you can go wrong here! My favourite was the bison dumpling but our group loved the spicy pork. Great cocktails but if you order Snakes on a Crane make sure you have an adventurous palette!!!

This is a one of the kind eatery. The depth of thoughts that has gone into the name, decor and menu (content and on both Chinese and English names) of the restaurant is exceptional. Thank you for providing the memorable dining experience.  I also wish to thank Ethan for providing the exceptional service and relating stories behind this great establishment.

Spectacular experience. The interior had the most magnificent command of colour and stunning design. The service was well coordinated and friendly even when all the tables were full. Drinks were creative and attractive as well as the food. If experiencing Baiju or dumpling is new, this place will put your neophobia to rest. As a person with an Asian heritage, I fully approve and appreciate the experience and effort put into the authenticity by the owner.

Had a fantastic evening here. Its an intimate spot and was incredibly busy so we were lucky to get in when we did, but well worth the wait. The dumplings are on a nother level, the staff was terrific, and the cocktail menu is wild. 100% coming back.
Cool dumplings. Expansive backroom, full of jazz and laowai-lowlifes, drinks and more dumplings. I heard a rumor and Snakes on a crane are both good drinks and compelling stories.

New fave spot! Between our table we ordered a wide variety of food, dumplings, and cocktails and everything was delicious. Service was top notch- vibe, ambience, and live music also were all bang on. These guys nailed it!
Speakeasies!!! Gotta say it s a pretty cool experience! Very cool vibe and creative menu!

Amazing ambience and creative cocktails. The live music was a great touch. Get the Snakes on a Crane or ask a server for a recommendation - their suggestions were spot on. New favorite bar in the city.

First off, fantastic experience from start to finish! Took my girlfriend and one of our roomates (who happens to be Asian) and we had an amazing time, the drinks and service were top notch and the idea of a speakeasy in today s times just feels cool. Conceptually this spot totally sets itself apart from the majority of big business dining experiences, and provides something new/unique that will only serve to further elevate the Vancouver restaurant scene. I have gotten to known one of the owners over the past few years and have had the pleasure of witnessing this project slowly form into what it is now.. it has truly been a labour of love for him and so impressive getting to see it come to life. On another note, I am very disappointed that people feel the need to attack new businesses starting up/pull the gentrification card, especially during the current economic climate for the hospitality industry. The owners have a great respect for the culture and the neighbourhood they have chosen for their venue. How is it fair to discredit and insult small business owners because their business doesn t reflect their skin colour? Would it be more acceptable if it were a sandwich shop? By that logic I guess an Asian person isn t allowed to run an Italian restaurant.. and maybe the Szechuan lettuce wraps/sushi rolls/poke bowls should be pulled from the menu at cactus club et al  Entrepreneurs and chefs should have the freedom to cook and serve and decorate however they feel like without small minded people putting them down. I would 100% recommend checking out this spot, and I hope people take these unfortunate negative reviews with a proper grain of salt.. check it out in person and make your own decision. Prepare to be blown away!
Awesome dumplings good atmosphere!

Such a cool space! got 3 number 7s for my friends and I and had such a great experience! our server was an expert and gave some wonderful recommendations. cant wait to tell all our friends about our time here

Phenomenal spot! Could not be happier with the experience as a whole! The space has been been incredibly designed and the cocktails are the best Ive had in Canada! I will be making an effort to return next time I visit Vancouver without a doubt.

What an awesome experience at Laowai! Something with such an edge here in Vancouver. You can tell that the owners definitely put a lot of time and effort into the space and menu - the cocktails were so delicious! Just went for drinks and to check the new space out after dinner. Excited to go back and try the dumplings!

Great food, great cocktails, and service. A fun speakeasy experience. Showed up at 6:30pm on a Thursday and was informed of a 30-45 minute wait, which we were notified via text when the table was ready (grabbed a quick drink at the Irish Heather across the street). Fun cocktails with a great story. The Bison Momo dumplings 10/10(so good had to order a second round!!), crispy eggplant 10/10(drool worthy), sweet and sour fried lingcod 9/10, would skip the vegetarian Shaomai dumplings, Xiao Long Bao was sold out unfortunately but will have to try them next time! Service was great and personable. Will definitely be back!

Vancouver needs more cool places like Laowai. Such a cool concept. Amazing decor. Knowledgeable staff. Food, cocktails and music were all fantastic. I cant wait to go back again. The place was slammed from the moment they opened...rightfully so... get there early. What a vibe.
Great food and awesome cocktails. Some of the most knowledgeable bartenders Ive met. Excellent vegan food options. Vegetarian options: Lots of good veggie and vegan options for food
Loved the food and super delicious cocktails!! Dumplings and the fried eggplant were unreal! Shared the table with 6 friends and Chris our server was amazing! Thanks for the great evening!
Really interesting and delicious cocktail menu and lots of vegan food options. Bartenders are super knowledgeable and the baiju menu is incredible. Worth going out of your way for.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi Tom, thanks for your kind word but you seem to have reviewed the wrong business. We are just a take out dumpling shop.

reviews.review_text: Best cocktails in Vancouver. If youre looking to get trashed on Jagerbombs (no judgement) you should probably go elsewhere. If youre looking for fun, imaginative cocktails made by expert bartenders, this is the spot for you. Great drinks, great service, great atmosphere.

When I heard Chinatown was getting a speakeasy I was SO EXCITED. I went on their opening night and wasnt disappointed - loved the decor, food was amazing (dumplings, fried eggplant and char siu were incredible). Its a cool, vibey atmosphere that Vancouver desperately needs more of! The dumpling bar is a new lunch favourite for sure. Lets also remember to give a little grace to restaurants right now, especially new ones opening after 16 months of lockdowns and restrictions. We should all be doing our best to support the small businesses that give life to our neighbourhoods :)
Great cocktails. Silly reviewers giving low stars because they didn t know the password. A simple google search would have solved that. It s a speakeasy ffs.
Been here twice now. Order the entire menu every time. Room is beautiful. Service is great. Cocktails are on point. Food is delicious... If you can find it.
Great dumplings and amazing lunch special in the heart of China Town!
Wowowoow be prepared for a wait but know that it s WORTH IT!!! The cocktails are presented at a level I ve seldom seen and the flavours of the dumplings had me welled up more than once. Do recommend.

I have to say. This has been one of the best expereince we had in a very long time! Took a while to get seated but when that was out of the way, the evening was simply great! China town needed this! And there it is! The food, wow! Different flavors mixed together. Delicious, delicious and delicious! Thank you to Alex. We will definitely by back!
The place looked really well done. Very nice touches to everything. Cocktails were creative and the food was well priced and delicious! Try the eggplant! I didnt know it could taste like that!
The dumplings at blind tiger are simply the best Ive had and the sauces really put them over the top. Hands down the best bar experience in Vancouver!

Great attention to detail in menu development and decor. It has been a long time coming seeing a place like this pop up in the Chinatown area. Great mix of patrons, thoughtful staff and boozy sips makes for a great mood and date night. Keep it up guys. Ill be back.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you for your review. We look forward to seeing you again soon!

reviews.review_text: Good food, good vibe. Loved the drink at the speakeasy. Only down side is the comment on the way I was dress at the entrance. But Ill still give a 5* for the vibe.

This place is incredible and is exactly what Vancouver needs more of. The food and drinks are awesome, and the general atmosphere of the space is very unique. You do not get an experience like this anywhere else in the City. Highly recommend.
Delicious, unique flavours and a cool aesthetic. Great new spot and who knows... there may be other surprises in store

Taku was incredible, he had a wealth of knowledge that blew us away! His technique along with ability to be so hospitable throughout our entire experience was truly inspiring. The food was to die for, the pork belly quite literally melts in your mouth. We will be recommending this place to everyone we know!! Liam and Nilanjana

Brook, the hostess out at the front is amazing! Huge credit to her for standing out in the cold, please at least provide more heaters, its winter time and shes there for hours freezing up. Despite all this, she maintains a great attitude and makes me feel very welcome.
Amazing food and drinks, staff are really knowledgeable and welcoming.  Cant wait to go back!

Robert Paulson would love this place! Its not for everyone, yaaaaa! We appreciate the efforts you take to keep it novel. Was our first experience with baijiu, hoping work our way through the menu. Thanks for bringing something new to the citys offerings.
Definitely try the cocktail  1 star review . What a delicious, delightful and cheeky way for a business to poke fun at and remove power from their antagonizers. Brilliant.
Here for the drinks. Love Lao wai in the back. definitely my go-to to kick off the weekend. Brings me back to asia

Excellent place in Chinatown for a drink or hang out with ur frds... no cellphone policy inside the restaurant... live music every weedend(if Im not mistaken their schedule)... highly recommend this place for everybody...
The staff was so nice. This Chinese inspired Speakeasy offers fancy cocktails, dumplings and other shared bites. Cheers!

Don t know why you would post awful reviews about a restaurant you know damn well just opened a few days ago. Especially during a time where restaurants and small businesses need our help the most. Shame on all of you. I digress, Louis was lovely and our experience in the beautiful restaurant was great. Don t listen to the people who couldn t get past the front door.
Best Dumplings in Chinatown which says something for sure. The debates about which are the best to order is what gets really spicy!

My first google review (I think) and this place was so wonderful. Food was great and the drinks were even better. Extremely friendly staff who are very knowledgeable and make you feel at home. Can t wait to come back!
Well worth the wait!! The place is stunning, the food was incredible, and the service was fantastic. Definitely try the crispy eggplant, and the cool cats and kittens (my fav drink on the menu)
Great experience  and good service.      Little on the pricey side but an enjoyable evening and one of a kind place.
Such an intricate and well-put cocktail menu. Never seen a place like this in Vancouver. Also Chey is the best mixologist Ive ever met
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi Laurie, thank your your kind words, we are just a simple dumpling shop and do not have a cocktail menu.

reviews.review_text: I love this place. The drinks and food are absolutely delicious. I would recommend 10/10. I love the staff, aesthetics, everything about this place is awesome.
Hidden gem in town! Best dumplings. Period!
Amazing food, amazing drinks and an even better atmosphere. Will be coming back many times in the future
Feeling very content and lucky to have stumbled on this place, these flavors, the kind staff, and the ambiance. I d eat here seven days a week if I could.
By far the coolest and best cocktail place in town. The bartenders are incredible. Cant wait to come back
Tasty vegetarian/ vegan dumplings and shumai!!
Order the number 7, you wont regret it. If possible get seated at the bar and if you are lucky you will get to meet Taku.
Don t forget to order the food off their secret menu
Love this place. friendly service, great food and amazing live music. The cocktail menu is well thoughtout~ Highly recommend
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi Edison, thank you for your kind words, but you seem to have reviewed the wrong business. We are just a small dumpling shop. We look forward to your next dumpling order!

reviews.review_text: Great cocktails and a very cool room. Nice to have another quality cocktail-focused lounge in Vancouver.

Such an amazing place from the getting in as a dumpling place to the surprise of getting into a hidden gem the decoration super beautiful, the staff are friendly,  the cocktail menu has nothing alike in Vancouver and the food is fantastic.
The dark speak easy has a long wait so arrive early to reserve your spot. The dumplings are all great but my favorite was the vegetarian and the bison.
Im not sure why there are so many reviews of a place that doesnt exist. If it did, Id go there for the tofu noodles and garlic eggplant, with a Khan And I cocktail.
